1
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:08,160
- Hey. - Hi.

2
00:00:08,210 --> 00:00:09,500
Pheebs, what's wrong?

3
00:00:09,550 --> 00:00:11,590
I'm just so exhausted from dragging around

4
00:00:11,640 --> 00:00:13,360
this huge engagement ring.

5
00:00:13,490 --> 00:00:14,890
Oh, my God.

6
00:00:14,950 --> 00:00:16,250
Congratulations.

7
00:00:16,420 --> 00:00:18,030
So did he get on one knee?

8
00:00:18,080 --> 00:00:19,740
Did he have a speech prepared?

9
00:00:19,790 --> 00:00:21,390
Oh, did he cry?

10
00:00:23,570 --> 00:00:26,210
Yeah, big surprise, I like proposals.

11
00:00:27,650 --> 00:00:29,430
Well, it was really sweet,

12
00:00:29,480 --> 00:00:31,670
and, like, the most romantic thing ever.

13
00:00:31,720 --> 00:00:33,420
Here's to Phoebe,

14
00:00:33,470 --> 00:00:35,260
who's found the greatest guy in the world.

15
00:00:35,310 --> 00:00:36,470
To Phoebe and--

16
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:38,210
I want to say "Mike"?

17
00:00:39,460 --> 00:00:40,700
To Phoebe and Mike.

18
00:00:41,820 --> 00:00:42,950
Thank you.

19
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:44,680
Oh, and I have something for you.

20
00:00:45,160 --> 00:00:46,690
It's my little black book.

21
00:00:46,740 --> 00:00:48,640
It's got the numbers of all the guys I've dated.

22
00:00:48,690 --> 00:00:52,030
Oh, Phoebe, that's nice,

23
00:00:52,080 --> 00:00:53,340
but you know what? I think I'm okay.

24
00:00:53,390 --> 00:00:54,220
Why don't you just give it

25
00:00:54,270 --> 00:00:55,630
to one of your other single girlfriends.

26
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:57,510
I would, but you're the last one.

27
00:00:59,930 --> 00:01:00,940
Give me the book!

28
00:01:02,970 --> 00:01:04,740
"Pablo Diaz.

29
00:01:04,790 --> 00:01:06,570
Brady Smith.

30
00:01:07,710 --> 00:01:09,500
Guy in Van"?

31
00:01:09,550 --> 00:01:11,100
Oh, my first love.

32
00:01:12,780 --> 00:01:14,670
What is the red X next to

33
00:01:14,670 --> 00:01:16,210
Bob Gremore's name mean?

34
00:01:16,260 --> 00:01:17,190
Dead.

35
00:01:19,410 --> 00:01:22,190
Oh, it's okay. No, he was old. Yeah.

36
00:01:22,750 --> 00:01:23,800
And he lived a full life.

37
00:01:23,850 --> 00:01:26,210
He was in the first wave at Omaha Beach.

38
00:01:23,850 --> 00:01:26,210
Omaha Beach:1944年诺曼底登陆中美军负责的一段

39
00:01:27,660 --> 00:01:29,650
oh, I'm sorry. I should've given you guys my black book

40
00:01:29,700 --> 00:01:30,880
when I got married.

41
00:01:30,930 --> 00:01:32,050
Although, it wasn't so much a book

42
00:01:32,100 --> 00:01:33,440
as a napkin.

43
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,060
With Janice's phone number on it.

44
00:01:38,110 --> 00:01:41,130
Phoebe, isn't Jethro Tull a band?

45
00:01:45,430 --> 00:01:46,890
Oh, yes, they are.

46
00:01:48,660 --> 00:01:50,890
《老友记》第十季第六集 罗斯的科研补助金

47
00:02:28,330 --> 00:02:29,360
Hey, honey.

48
00:02:30,580 --> 00:02:31,590
Hey, sweetie.

49
00:02:32,790 --> 00:02:34,110
- Is Monica not here? - No.

50
00:02:34,380 --> 00:02:35,650
Then I'll tell you.

51
00:02:35,700 --> 00:02:38,430
My agency was bidding for a big account, and they got it.

52
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:40,130
It's my first national commercial.

53
00:02:40,180 --> 00:02:40,950
Cool.

54
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:41,980
And I don't want to brag,

55
00:02:42,030 --> 00:02:43,770
but a lot of the ideas were mine.

56
00:02:44,300 --> 00:02:45,480
Hell, you weren't there.

57
00:02:45,530 --> 00:02:46,870
All the ideas were mine.

58
00:02:47,540 --> 00:02:48,870
That's great.

59
00:02:48,920 --> 00:02:51,160
Hey, can you cast me in it?

60
00:02:51,830 --> 00:02:54,400
I really don't think you're right for the part.

61
00:02:54,450 --> 00:02:55,970
What do you mean? I can do anything.

62
00:02:56,020 --> 00:02:57,530
I'm a chameleon.

63
00:02:59,530 --> 00:03:00,820
I'm old.

64
00:03:02,940 --> 00:03:04,350
I'm tired.

65
00:03:05,260 --> 00:03:07,350
Oh, I am hot. I'm cold.

66
00:03:07,400 --> 00:03:09,650
Come on, what can't I do?

67
00:03:10,820 --> 00:03:12,970
First of all, bravo.

68
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,970
But I don't think you're right for this.

69
00:03:16,020 --> 00:03:18,240
The part's a stuffy college professor.

70
00:03:18,290 --> 00:03:19,710
I can do that.

71
00:03:19,930 --> 00:03:22,200
Hello, I'm your professor.

72
00:03:22,450 --> 00:03:24,610
When I'm not busy thinking of important things,

73
00:03:24,660 --> 00:03:26,870
or professing...

74
00:03:27,980 --> 00:03:30,290
...l like to use-- What's the product?

75
00:03:30,490 --> 00:03:34,000
Software that facilitates inter-business networking e-solutions.

76
00:03:39,170 --> 00:03:40,480
I'm cold.

77
00:03:43,550 --> 00:03:44,850
- Hey. - Hey.

78
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:45,980
Guess who's a finalist

79
00:03:46,030 --> 00:03:48,050
for a huge research grant?

80
00:03:48,100 --> 00:03:49,040
I'll give you a hint.

81
00:03:49,090 --> 00:03:50,210
He's looking right at you.

82
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:53,200
Well, unless it's the creepy guy

83
00:03:53,250 --> 00:03:54,790
with his hand up his kilt...

84
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:56,690
...I'm gonna say, "Congratulations."

85
00:03:57,360 --> 00:03:58,860
I'm so excited.

86
00:03:58,910 --> 00:04:02,230
Apparently, I beat out hundreds of other applicants...

87
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:05,060
...including five guys I went to graduate school with.

88
00:04:05,110 --> 00:04:07,870
Not that I'm keeping score, or anything. Five.

89
00:04:08,900 --> 00:04:10,740
- Wow, that's great. - Yeah.

90
00:04:10,790 --> 00:04:11,830
So tell me about the grant.

91
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:13,890
Well, okay, it's for $25,000.

92
00:04:14,030 --> 00:04:15,070
And if I get it,

93
00:04:15,070 --> 00:04:17,540
I'll be able to complete my field research.

94
00:04:17,590 --> 00:04:19,590
And there will be an article about me

95
00:04:19,640 --> 00:04:21,540
in the <i>Paleontology Review</i>.

96
00:04:21,590 --> 00:04:23,770
It'll be the first time my name is in there...

97
00:04:23,820 --> 00:04:26,460
...without people raising serious questions about my work.

98
00:04:27,940 --> 00:04:30,210
Are you talking about the Dewer Grant?

99
00:04:30,260 --> 00:04:31,220
Yeah. Why?

100
00:04:31,270 --> 00:04:33,560
Benjamin Hobart is administering that grant.

101
00:04:33,610 --> 00:04:35,760
- Your ex-boyfriend? - Yeah.

102
00:04:35,810 --> 00:04:38,080
So your ex-boyfriend is gonna determine

103
00:04:38,130 --> 00:04:40,400
if your new boyfriend gets this grant?

104
00:04:40,450 --> 00:04:42,470
Wow, your new boyfriend is screwed.

105
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:46,080
No. No, we ended on great terms.

106
00:04:46,130 --> 00:04:46,840
I mean if anything,

107
00:04:46,890 --> 00:04:48,080
I think this could help you. You know what?

108
00:04:48,130 --> 00:04:50,440
Why don't we all go out to dinner,

109
00:04:50,490 --> 00:04:51,710
and I can introduce you.

110
00:04:52,130 --> 00:04:53,360
If you think it'd help.

111
00:04:53,410 --> 00:04:55,110
Yeah, absolutely. I'll call him.

112
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:58,030
Now, is there anything I could do to butter him up?

113
00:04:58,080 --> 00:04:59,790
Anything he really likes?

114
00:05:01,170 --> 00:05:03,280
He does have a pretty serious latex fetish.

115
00:05:03,330 --> 00:05:04,880
We'll see how dinner goes.

116
00:05:09,950 --> 00:05:12,160
- Hey. - Hey, you want to go see a movie?

117
00:05:12,950 --> 00:05:15,310
I told you I had to spend all day clearing out stuff

118
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:16,560
so Mike could move in.

119
00:05:16,610 --> 00:05:18,180
- Oh, right. - Yeah.

120
00:05:18,230 --> 00:05:20,290
Now that I'm here,

121
00:05:20,340 --> 00:05:22,690
I might as well help with the cleaning and organizing.

122
00:05:22,740 --> 00:05:25,150
I just happen to have my label maker.

123
00:05:26,860 --> 00:05:29,440
Oh, it's so hard to get rid of stuff.

124
00:05:29,490 --> 00:05:31,450
Did you and Chandler make compromises

125
00:05:31,500 --> 00:05:32,910
when you moved in together?

126
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:34,450
Chandler did.

127
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:37,040
What does he want you to give up?

128
00:05:37,090 --> 00:05:38,200
A bunch of stuff.

129
00:05:38,250 --> 00:05:39,590
And the worst one,

130
00:05:39,640 --> 00:05:41,540
he wants me to get rid of Gladys.

131
00:05:41,820 --> 00:05:43,240
Who's Gladys?

132
00:05:47,540 --> 00:05:49,260
What a tragic loss.

133
00:05:50,310 --> 00:05:52,450
Yeah, I really hate to give her up.

134
00:05:52,770 --> 00:05:54,890
Oh, I know. Oh, you should take her.

135
00:05:57,630 --> 00:06:00,080
I don't know.

136
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:02,690
What, you don't like her?

137
00:06:02,740 --> 00:06:06,190
Of course I do. What's not to like?

138
00:06:07,300 --> 00:06:08,720
I'd take her in a minute.

139
00:06:09,740 --> 00:06:11,920
But I think that you're giving up too easy.

140
00:06:11,970 --> 00:06:14,230
Honey, I think that you need to fight for her.

141
00:06:15,470 --> 00:06:17,590
- Really, you think? - Absolutely.

142
00:06:17,640 --> 00:06:18,860
You say to him,

143
00:06:18,910 --> 00:06:20,880
"I'm sorry, Mike, I can't live without her.

144
00:06:20,930 --> 00:06:22,800
She means too much to me."

145
00:06:23,550 --> 00:06:26,380
Okay, I'll fight for her. Okay.

146
00:06:27,140 --> 00:06:29,400
Oh, wait. I just realized, if I do that,

147
00:06:29,450 --> 00:06:30,670
that means you don't get her.

148
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:32,780
Damn it, I did not think this through.

149
00:06:36,830 --> 00:06:38,790
- Hey, guys. - Hey.

150
00:06:38,790 --> 00:06:40,690
Oh, any word on casting yet?

151
00:06:40,740 --> 00:06:42,860
I told you, you're not right for the part.

152
00:06:42,910 --> 00:06:44,070
What do you mean?

153
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:45,800
Rach, don't I seem like a professor

154
00:06:45,850 --> 00:06:48,010
you'd buy some kind of e-crap from?

155
00:06:49,290 --> 00:06:50,080
I'm sorry,

156
00:06:50,130 --> 00:06:52,340
this sounds like something I'm never gonna be interested in.

157
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:55,260
Look, come on, please?

158
00:06:55,310 --> 00:06:58,140
It's not like I'm asking you for some crazy favor.

159
00:06:58,300 --> 00:06:59,360
This is what I do for a living.

160
00:06:59,410 --> 00:07:01,170
I am a professional actor.

161
00:07:01,220 --> 00:07:03,300
Man, I'm two hours late for work.

162
00:07:05,060 --> 00:07:06,490
Here's a copy of my reel.

163
00:07:06,540 --> 00:07:08,370
It's got all the commercials that I've been in.

164
00:07:08,420 --> 00:07:10,230
- Joe-- - Just watch it.

165
00:07:10,280 --> 00:07:11,110
If you don't like it,

166
00:07:11,160 --> 00:07:13,130
don't pass it on to your bosses.

167
00:07:13,430 --> 00:07:15,420
- Fine. - Thank you.

168
00:07:20,070 --> 00:07:22,460
- Work, Joe. - Damn it.

169
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:27,410
What am I gonna do now?

170
00:07:27,460 --> 00:07:28,730
Just pass the tape along.

171
00:07:28,780 --> 00:07:30,510
He's not right for the part.

172
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:31,470
If I suggest him,

173
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:33,220
my bosses will think I'm an idiot.

174
00:07:33,270 --> 00:07:35,450
And that's something they should learn on their own.

175
00:07:36,180 --> 00:07:38,460
Just tell Joey that you watched the tape...

176
00:07:38,510 --> 00:07:40,630
...and you liked it, but your bosses didn't.

177
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:41,960
Then that way, you're the good guy,

178
00:07:42,010 --> 00:07:43,320
and they're the bad guy.

179
00:07:43,370 --> 00:07:45,850
That's good. I liked it, they didn't.

180
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:50,910
Joey, for God's sake, go to work.

181
00:07:56,030 --> 00:07:59,220
I can't believe I'm about to meet Benjamin Hobart.

182
00:07:59,270 --> 00:08:01,340
I've always thought of him as someone I'd invite...

183
00:08:01,390 --> 00:08:04,120
...to my fantasy dinner party.

184
00:08:05,250 --> 00:08:06,330
Do you think there's any chance

185
00:08:06,380 --> 00:08:08,730
he'll bring Christie Brinkley or C-3PO?

186
00:08:10,590 --> 00:08:12,780
Sorry, it looks like it's just him.

187
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:16,080
Charlie.

188
00:08:18,540 --> 00:08:22,620
My God, you look absolutely stunning.

189
00:08:22,670 --> 00:08:25,640
Well, I am having a good hair day.

190
00:08:26,660 --> 00:08:29,880
- It's so good to see you. - Oh, you too.

191
00:08:33,860 --> 00:08:35,160
I'm okay.

192
00:08:36,380 --> 00:08:39,430
I'm sorry. Ross Geller, Benjamin Hobart.

193
00:08:39,480 --> 00:08:41,170
It's an honor to meet you.

194
00:08:41,220 --> 00:08:43,320
I can't tell you how long...

195
00:08:43,370 --> 00:08:47,620
...I've been an admirer of your work. I mean, that Nobel Prize.

196
00:08:49,470 --> 00:08:51,240
I mean, I have to tell you

197
00:08:51,290 --> 00:08:53,980
that you're one of the reasons I got into the field.

198
00:08:54,330 --> 00:08:56,010
Well, likewise.

199
00:08:56,580 --> 00:08:58,420
Actually not likewise.

200
00:08:58,470 --> 00:09:00,170
I'd never heard of you until this morning.

201
00:09:00,220 --> 00:09:01,940
But it's nice to be nice.

202
00:09:03,820 --> 00:09:06,660
- Shall we? - Yeah. Thank you.

203
00:09:10,140 --> 00:09:13,240
I can't believe that you chose this restaurant.

204
00:09:13,830 --> 00:09:15,070
Do you remember the night?

205
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:17,680
Oh, my God. I completely forgot.

206
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:22,730
Oh, my God, I can't believe they let us back in this place.

207
00:09:30,420 --> 00:09:31,860
You weren't there.

208
00:09:33,350 --> 00:09:36,660
No, but, you know, it's just a funny image.

209
00:09:36,710 --> 00:09:41,340
You know, the two of you in this restaurant with the....

210
00:09:43,730 --> 00:09:45,920
Ross, why don't you tell Benji

211
00:09:45,970 --> 00:09:48,230
about your proposal while I go to the ladies' room.

212
00:09:50,660 --> 00:09:52,570
So tell me about it.

213
00:09:52,620 --> 00:09:56,870
Painted Desert:在亚利桑那州北部

214
00:09:52,620 --> 00:09:56,870
Okay. Well, I would like to do a dig in the Painted Desert.

215
00:09:56,920 --> 00:10:00,580
There are still several areas that haven't been fully excavated.

216
00:10:00,630 --> 00:10:01,940
- Break up with Charlie. - What?

217
00:10:01,990 --> 00:10:02,710
What?

218
00:10:04,540 --> 00:10:08,800
Did you just say, "Break up with Charlie"?

219
00:10:09,830 --> 00:10:11,450
Well, yes and no.

220
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:14,430
Yes, I did say it. And no, I didn't not say it.

221
00:10:16,030 --> 00:10:18,260
Kind of inappropriate, don't you think?

222
00:10:18,310 --> 00:10:20,230
Listen, I'm sorry.

223
00:10:20,280 --> 00:10:21,650
I just haven't seen her for so long,

224
00:10:21,700 --> 00:10:23,770
all these feelings are rushing back.

225
00:10:23,820 --> 00:10:24,790
I'm starting to realize

226
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:26,460
how much I've missed her.

227
00:10:26,510 --> 00:10:28,820
And I'm gonna need you to break up with her.

228
00:10:30,960 --> 00:10:32,510
Are you serious?

229
00:10:32,560 --> 00:10:33,950
If you say, yes, then I'm serious.

230
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,810
If you say, no, then I'm joking.

231
00:10:37,520 --> 00:10:39,360
- No. - Joking it is.

232
00:10:43,670 --> 00:10:45,120
Hi, sorry I'm late.

233
00:10:45,170 --> 00:10:46,580
Hey, how'd it go with Mike?

234
00:10:46,630 --> 00:10:48,000
Is he gonna let you keep the painting?

235
00:10:48,050 --> 00:10:50,390
No, he really hates it.

236
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:53,460
But he's gonna let me keep my box of human hair.

237
00:10:54,880 --> 00:10:56,840
So you gotta pick your battles.

238
00:10:57,350 --> 00:11:00,250
But the good news is, Gladys is yours.

239
00:11:02,050 --> 00:11:03,790
Wow, what's the bad news?

240
00:11:04,970 --> 00:11:06,110
Who's Gladys?

241
00:11:06,230 --> 00:11:08,320
Oh, she's that work of art I made.

242
00:11:08,370 --> 00:11:10,600
You know, with the woman coming out of the frame.

243
00:11:11,480 --> 00:11:14,910
And Monica gets to keep her?

244
00:11:15,890 --> 00:11:19,200
In her house? I am so jealous.

245
00:11:20,930 --> 00:11:23,170
I didn't know you wanted her too.

246
00:11:25,180 --> 00:11:28,050
Well, I mean, sure, of course.

247
00:11:29,130 --> 00:11:31,430
But you already gave that to Monica, so....

248
00:11:31,480 --> 00:11:33,600
You know, I would give her up for you.

249
00:11:33,650 --> 00:11:35,150
No, I couldn't let you do that.

250
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:37,730
- No, but I want to. - But I don't want you to.

251
00:11:37,780 --> 00:11:41,870
- But I insist. - But I insist harder.

252
00:11:43,520 --> 00:11:46,140
Girls. Girls. Stop. Okay, we'll flip a coin.

253
00:11:46,190 --> 00:11:47,150
Heads, she's Rachel's.

254
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:48,490
Tails, she's Monica's.

255
00:11:51,780 --> 00:11:53,600
Tails. Monica, she's yours.

256
00:11:53,650 --> 00:11:55,600
No, that landed in your food.

257
00:11:56,680 --> 00:11:57,770
No, no, that's okay.

258
00:11:57,820 --> 00:12:00,210
You won fair and square. I'm so sad.

259
00:12:04,120 --> 00:12:05,180
Hey, Joe?

260
00:12:05,180 --> 00:12:06,910
- What's up? - Bad news.

261
00:12:06,910 --> 00:12:07,770
I watched the tape

262
00:12:07,770 --> 00:12:09,130
and passed it along to my bosses

263
00:12:09,130 --> 00:12:10,860
and they weren't interested.

264
00:12:12,750 --> 00:12:14,180
I'm sorry, man.

265
00:12:16,710 --> 00:12:18,570
But you watched the tape?

266
00:12:18,620 --> 00:12:20,890
Yeah, I liked it.

